<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38206b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38206b">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38206b"> 206(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cold tale</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Burton is quoting Von Hammer&apos;s opinion on the <i>Haz&aacute;r Afs&aacute;nah</i>]</font> It containeth a thousand nights, but less than two hundred night-stories, for a single history often occupied several nights. I have seen it complete sundry times; and it is, in truth, a corrupted book of <mark>cold tales</mark>. <font color="green">[Footnoted by Burton]</font> <i>i.e.</i> of silly anecdotes. <small> Richard F. Burton, &ldquo;Terminal Essay&rdquo;, <a name="RBTE1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE1"><cite title="source">The Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) X, 73</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
